properties.areaDesc: North Snowy Range Foothills; Central Carbon County
properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued February 29 at 2:05AM MST until March 2 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...MODERATE TO HEAVY SNOW AT TIMES WILL IMPACT AREAS ALONG AND
WEST OF THE LARAMIE RANGE SUNDAY THROUGH MONDAY MORNING...

* WHAT...Heavy snow and patchy blowing snow possible. Total snow
accumulations of 4 to 8 inches expected. Winds could gust as
high as 40 mph resulting in visibilities near zero at times.

* WHERE...Central and western Carbon County to include
Rawlins...Sinclair...Elk Mountain and Arlington.

* WHEN...From late tonight through late Sunday night.

* IMPACTS...Transportation may be severely impacted with snow
covered roads...blowing snow and poor visibility. Plan on
slippery road conditions. Areas of blowing snow could
significantly reduce visibility.
properties.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH NOW IN EFFECT FROM LATE TONIGHT THROUGH LATE SUNDAY NIGHT
